Package net.vivialconnect.model.error

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    MessageError
    Intermediary class for parse errors that occur at API-level.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ApiRequestException
    This is exception is thrown when an error occurs during a API request, specifically when the error is not cause by: - Unauthorized access.
    BadRequestException
    Exception for Bad Request error returned by the API.
    ForbiddenAccessException
    Exception for Forbidden Access error returned by the API.
    MessageErrorException
    Exception when an error occurs during a message send.
    NoContentException
    Exception for responses without a payload.
    RateLimitException
    Exception when a rate limit is reached in a API endpoint.
    ResourceNotFoundException
    Exception when an entity is not found.
    ServerErrorException
    Exception when a server error happens.
    UnauthorizedAccessException
    Exception for unauthorized access error.
    VivialConnectException
    Map errors that occur at API-level.
